# Event Booking System

Production-ready REST API for event booking and queue management built with Node.js, TypeScript, MongoDB, and Redis.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer           | Technology                                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Runtime         | Node.js + TypeScript                        |
| Framework       | Express.js                                  |
| Database        | MongoDB (Mongoose)                          |
| Cache / Queue   | Redis (ioredis)                             |
| Background Jobs | BullMQ                                      |
| Auth            | JWT + Refresh Token Rotation + Google OAuth |
| File Upload     | Multer + Cloudinary                         |
| Email           | Nodemailer                                  |
| Real-time       | Socket.io + Redis Adapter                   |
| Validation      | Zod                                         |
| Logging         | Pino                                        |

---

## Features

- **Auth** — Register, Email OTP verification, Login, Refresh token rotation, Logout
- **Google OAuth** — Login with Google (Passport.js)
- **Password** — Forget / Reset via OTP, Change password
- **Profile Image** — Upload / Replace via Cloudinary
- **Providers** — Create provider profile, generate time slots
- **Slots** — View available slots with real-time availability
- **Bookings** — Atomic booking with Lua scripts, auto-expiry via BullMQ
- **Queue** — FIFO waitlist, auto-promotion when slot frees up
- **Real-time** — WebSocket notifications for queue events
- **Admin** — Delete users

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── config/           # env, database, redis, passport, cloudinary, logger
├── types/            # enums, errors, express.d.ts
├── utils/            # async-handler, lua-scripts, slot-generator
├── services/         # cache, lock, email, otp, websocket, cloudinary
├── middleware/        # authenticate, authorize, validate, rate-limit, multer, idempotency, error-handler
├── models/           # User, Provider, Slot, Booking, QueueEntry
├── modules/
│   ├── auth/         # schema · service · controller · routes · token.service
│   ├── provider/     # schema · service · controller · routes
│   ├── slot/         # schema · service · controller · routes · slot.cache
│   ├── booking/      # schema · service · controller · routes
│   └── queue/        # service · controller · routes
├── workers/          # expiration · promotion · queue-confirmation-expiry · notification · queue.definitions
├── app.ts            # Express setup
└── server.ts         # HTTP + WebSocket startup + graceful shutdown
```

---

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root:

```dotenv
# App
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# MongoDB
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/booking-system

# Redis
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# JWT
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=your-access-secret-must-be-at-least-32-chars
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-refresh-secret-must-be-at-least-32-chars
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRES_IN=15m
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN=7d
COOKIE_SECRET=your-cookie-secret-must-be-at-least-32-chars

# Email (SMTP)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your@email.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=your@email.com

# Google OAuth
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/google/callback

# Cloudinary
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your-api-key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your-api-secret

# Config
BCRYPT_ROUNDS=12
OTP_LENGTH=6
OTP_EXPIRES_MINUTES=10
BOOKING_EXPIRY_MINUTES=15
QUEUE_CONFIRM_MINUTES=10
CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=60
LOCK_TTL_MS=10000
SLOT_GENERATE_MAX_DAYS=90
```

